@NODE About "About"

@{b}NAME@{ub}
About

@{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
About

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
Corresponds to choosing the menu item About.  Shows some  information about the
version, the author, etc.

@{b}INPUT PARAMETERS@{ub}
---

@{b}RESULTS@{ub}
RC:
 always 0
Result:
  N.A.

@{b}BUGS@{ub}
---

@{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
---

@ENDNODE

@NODE AddFractal "AddFractal"

@{b}NAME@{ub}
AddFractal

@{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
AddFractal JULIA/S MANDEL/S BIFURCATION/S DYNAMICSYSTEM/S PLASMA/S LYAPUNOV/S

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
This command adds a new fractal of the given type to the list and initializes it
with the standard parameters for the type.

@{b}INPUT PARAMETERS@{ub}
Keywords for the different fractal types.

@{b}RESULTS@{ub}
RC:
  5 ... fractaltype unknown
  8 ... too few parameters
 10 ... error during creation, most likely not enough memory
Result:
 Name of the newly added fractal

@{b}BUGS@{ub}
---

@{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
---

@ENDNODE

@NODE BoxZoom "BoxZoom"

@{b}NAME@{ub}
BoxZoom

@{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
BoxZoom <Fractalname>/A <In>/A/N

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
Just the same as choosing the menu item 'BoxZoom in/Out'.

@{b}INPUT PARAMETERS@{ub}
<Fractalname> : Name of a fractal
<In>          : This is a number, if equal to 0, it means BoxZoom out, otherwise
                BoxZoom in...

@{b}RESULTS@{ub}
RC:
 3 ... fractal not calculated
 5 ... fractalname unknown
 8 ... too few parameters
Result:
 N.A.

@{b}BUGS@{ub}
---

@{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
---

@ENDNODE

@NODE CalcFract "CalcFract"

@{b}NAME@{ub}
CalcFract

@{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
CalcFract <Fractalname>/A <LeftEdge>/A/N <TopEdge>/A/N <Width>/A/N <Height>/A/N

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
Corresponds to  choosing the gadget  'Calculate picture'. But here you can also
define the screen coordinates for the window.

@{b}INPUT PARAMETERS@{ub}
<Fractalname> : Name of a fractal
<LeftEdge>
<TopEdge>
<Width>
<Height>      : Numbers,  which define the  position and size  of the window. A
                virtual  coordinate-system  with a resolution of 10000x10000 is
                used.  If a coordinate is negative,  then the default value for
                this item is used.

@{b}RESULTS@{ub}
RC:
  5  ... fractal unknown
  8  ... too few parameters
 10  ... not enough memory
Result:
 N.A.

@{b}BUGS@{ub}
---

@{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
@{"DelCalced" LINK "DelCalced"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE ChangeFractName "ChangeFractName"

@{b}NAME@{ub}
ChangeFractName

@{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
ChangeFractName <Old name>/A <New name>/A

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
Changes the name of the fractal. The name is always converted to uppercase, spaces
are replaced by a '_'.  The name is made  unique, i.e. if  already another fractal
with the same name exists, then a number is appended.

@{b}INPUT PARAMETERS@{ub}
<Old name> : Name of the fractal, whose name should be changed
<New name> : New name for this fractal

@{b}RESULTS@{ub}
RC:
 5 ... fractal <Old name> is unknown
 8 ... too few parameters
Result:
 New name of the fractal

@{b}BUGS@{ub}
---

@{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
---

@ENDNODE

@NODE ChangePaletteName "ChangePaletteName"

@{b}NAME@{ub}
ChangePaletteName

@{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
ChangePaletteName <Old name>/A <New name>/A

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
Alters the name of a palette.

@{b}INPUT PARAMETERS@{ub}
<Old name> : Name of the palette
<New name> : New name for this palette

@{b}RESULTS@{ub}
RC:
 5 ... palette not found
 8 ... too few parameters
Result:
 new name for the palette

@{b}BUGS@{ub}
---

@{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
---

@ENDNODE

@NODE ChoiceRequest "ChoiceRequest"

@{b}NAME@{ub}
ChoiceRequest

@{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
ChoiceRequest <Body> <Choices>

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
Creates and shows  a requester with the content <Body> and lets the user choose
something...

@{b}INPUT PARAMETERS@{ub}
<Body>    : Bodytext.
<Choices> : Choices, separarated by '|'

@{b}RESULTS@{ub}
RC:
 0 ... user has choosed, result in Result
 8 ... too few parameters
Result:
 choice (intuition-conform)

@{b}Example@{ub}
ChoiceRequest "Please choose a number..." "1|2|3|Abort"

A requester appears, which looks like follows:

|----------------------------|
|                            |
| Please choose a number...  |
|                            |
|                            |
|  1     2     3      Abort  |
|                            |
|----------------------------|
   ^     ^     ^       ^
   |     |     |       |
  '1'   '2'   '3'     '0'   <- choicenumber, placed in Result

Attention:
The rightmost choice has always the codenumber 0, because it's always ment to be
some  kind  of  'Abort'.  The  other  choices have  numbers from  left to right,
starting with 1.

@{b}BUGS@{ub}
RexxMast  does  some  string-conversions. Normally it's possible, to start a new
line  with  '\n',  but  Arexx  replaces  the  backslash '\' by '\\',  makeing it
impossible to start a new line in the body.

@{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
---

@ENDNODE

