@NODE LoadPicData "LoadPicData"

@{b}NAME@{ub}
LoadPicData <Name>/A
LoadPicData

@{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
LoadPicData <Name>/A
LoadPicData

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
Loads the data of a fractal picture and inserts it into the picture  list at the
right place.  Base  directory  is  the  directory,  from  which  the program was
started, i.e. PROGDIR:
If <Name> isn't specified, then a filerequester appears.  In  this case 'Result'
isn't defined (because you can load several files at once using filemultiselect)

@{b}INPUT PARAMETERS@{ub}
<Name> : filename of the picture data to load

@{b}RESULTS@{ub}
RC:
 5 ... error
 8 ... wrong number of parameters
Result:
 name of the new fractal picture, if name was specified

@{b}BUGS@{ub}
---

